%description:

Protocol Test Framework -- example opp_test wrapper.

Runs the `tcp_handshake_seq` ProtocolTest program: it observes host1's TCP three-way
handshake at the transport layer (SYN sent, SYN+ACK received acknowledging ISN+1, final
ACK sent) and emits a PASS/FAIL verdict line. The test passes when the framework prints
"PROTOCOLTEST tcp_handshake_seq: PASS".

This file illustrates how a ProtocolTest is wrapped as an opp_test `.test` case for a CI
run: select a scenario + the program name via the ProtocolTester's `testName`, then assert
the verdict line with a contains-check. The prebuilt framework library and its NED are loaded
with the -l/-n arguments (adjust the paths to your build); wiring this into INET's
fingerprint/CI runner is the separate harness step.

%extraargs: -l ../lib/libprotocoltest.so -n ../../../src;../lib

%inifile: omnetpp.ini

[General]
network = ProtocolTestDemo
sim-time-limit = 1s
seed-set = 0

# host1 opens a TCP connection to host2's echo server.
*.host1.numApps = 1
*.host1.app[0].typename = "TcpSessionApp"
*.host1.app[0].connectAddress = "host2"
*.host1.app[0].connectPort = 1000
*.host1.app[0].tOpen = 0.1s
*.host1.app[0].tSend = 0.2s
*.host1.app[0].sendBytes = 100B
*.host1.app[0].tClose = 2s
*.host2.numApps = 1
*.host2.app[0].typename = "TcpEchoApp"
*.host2.app[0].localPort = 1000

# select the protocol-test program to run
*.tester.testName = "tcp_handshake_seq"

%contains: stdout
PROTOCOLTEST tcp_handshake_seq: PASS
